citeinfo.title: DTrans_ssxx0pcb: ZIP Code Boundaries
citeinfo.othercit: Data file format ssxx0pcb: ss=State abbreviation; pcb=ZIP Code Boundary layer abbreviation. Note: Some Dynamap(R)/2000 GIS formats may have other file naming conventions for this layer.

descript.abstract: The Dynamap(R)/Transportation ZIP Code Boundary layer is a cartographic representation derived from the most current information available from the United States Postal Service street delivery information. The Tele Atlas(R) database contains representations for all U.S. and Puerto Rico 5-digit postal codes and includes changes that have occurred within the preceding quarter.
descript.purpose: The purpose of this layer is to provide to users who need them the most current cartographic representations of USPS ZIP Code information.
descript.supplinf: To find out more about Dynamap(R) Transportation and other available products, visit http://www.teleatlas.com.

status.update: The Tele Atlas(R) database receives monthly updates from the United States Postal Service. Every quarter (January, April, July and October) Tele Atlas(R) releases new updated ZIP Code boundary and point files.

dataqual.logic: All segment strings that form the ZIP Code boundaries must have closure to form polygons. ZIP Code boundaries are generalized.
dataqual.complete: The number of ZIP Code boundaries created each quarter is checked against the total in the Tele Atlas(R) database. The Tele Atlas(R) database represents the most current ZIP Code information from the United States Postal Service. After processing, the dataset is checked for drawing display, correct number of records, file sizes and then compared with the contents of the Tele Atlas(R) database at the time of creation.

horizpa.horizpar: The ZIP Code Boundary layer allows for six implied decimal places of precision. However, horizontal positional accuracy for this layer is not tested.

procstep.procdesc: Tele Atlas(R) extracts the dataset quarterly from the Tele Atlas(R) database using proprietary software. Data then is converted into multiple GIS formats. ISO quality standards are enforced throughout the production process.

altsys.altenc: Explicit elevation coordinate included with horizontal coordinates

overview.eaover: Entity Overview: ZIP Code boundaries were developed from street delivery 5-digit ZIP Codes. These polygons identify areas where mail is delivered (from a city block or two to a whole rural town). Attribute Overview (Attribution information for this entity varies depending on GIS format produced. Below are attribute fields common to most formats. For more detail, see the Entity and Attribution Detail Citation section.): * Name: ZIP Codes with one or more post offices may serve many localities. The term 'Name' is associated with an area inside a ZIP, which could include towns, parts of towns, airports and office complexes. When these have been defined, Tele Atlas(R) includes them in the Name field in the boundary and inventory files and, in some formats, in a separate Alternate Name file. Place names are listed together for each ZIP Code, with the principal station in that ZIP not necessarily listed first. Where no place name was listed in the USPS City/State File, the parent post office name was used. If both fields were blank in the USPS City/State File, this field may be blank. The area and centroid fields for such entries represent the area and centroid for the entire ZIP Code. Therefore, these fields will be identical for all entries with the same ZIP Code. * St_FIPS: The 2-digit state FIPS code where the ZIP Code is located. * Cty_FIPS: The 3-digit county FIPS code where the ZIP Code is located. * Key: The 5-digit postal code. 1st digit = '0': The USPS divides the country into 10 geographical areas and assigns numbers 0-9 to correspond to each area. For ZIP Code 05602: the first digit = 0 represents ZIP Codes in the Northeast United States. 2nd digit = '5': The 2nd digit is a subdivision area of the first. '5' = subdivision of the State of Vermont in the '0' area. 3rd digit = '6': The 3rd digit is a further subdivision. The 3rd digit along with the first 2 digits represents an area serviced by a Post Office Sectional Center Facility. '056' = Sectional Center Facility servicing the Montpelier, VT area. 4th and 5th digits = '0' and '2': The 4th and 5th digits further subdivide a geographical region. '05602' is the ZIP Code for Montpelier, Vermont.
